Reasoning: The paper deals with differential privacy in the context of database queries, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.DB sub-category. However, the use of calculus and the notion of derivative sensitivity also suggest that it could belong to the cs.CR (cryptography and security), cs.IT (information theory), or cs.LG (machine learning) sub-categories. Finally, the implementation and evaluation of the analyzer suggest that it could also belong to the cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) sub-category.
